ream waves in terms the wavefront extension,\norientation or their wavelength. However some features are conserved in the\nFourier spectra of downstream compressive waves that present a bump or\nflattening at wavelengths approximately corresponding to those of the upstream\nULF waves. In the transverse downstream spectra these features are weaker.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 25 Jan 2022 19:30:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-27"}
