ize. On the night following impact the comet was\nstill substantially brighter than before impact, but R-I had returned to its\npre-impact value. B-R remained significantly redder. The ejecta 25 hours after\nimpact was fan-shaped subtending ~180{\\deg} roughly symmetrical about position\nangle 225{\\deg}. The mean expansion velocity 90{\\deg} from the direction to the\nSun was 185{\\deg} 12 m s-1.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 26 Jan 2022 03:10:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-27"}
